display.description: The Meticulous cannot replicate the initial super-high flow of water onto the puck given by an LR, but the initial drop of the water column followed by a full-power piston move is the closest we can get.  After that, this profile attempts to emulate the phase where you hold the lever up to allow the preinfusion to happen at 3 bar until the bottom of the basket is covered and a few drops hit the cup, followed by releasing the lever to allow the spring to apply its force-curve as it compresses the water through the puck.  You will need to control this one primarily by your grind size, similar to a real LR.  The values in the extraction phase for the pressure curve were the best online estimates from LR owners that were able to get approximate pressure indications since the LR doesn't have a pressure guage and they don't publish exact specs for their springs or force curves.
